==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Nightshade
<hw>Night"shade`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>nichtscadu</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A common name of
many species of the genus <gen>Solanum</gen>, given esp. to the
<spn>Solanum nigrum</spn>, or black nightshade, a low, branching weed
with small white flowers and black berries reputed to be
poisonous.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Deadly nightshade</b></col>. <cd>Same as
<er>Belladonna</er> <sd>(a)</sd>.</cd> -- <col><b>Enchanter's
nightshade</b></col>. <cd>See under <er>Enchanter</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Stinking nightshade</b></col>. <cd>See <er>Henbane</er>.</cd> --
<col><b>Three-leaved nightshade</b></col>. <cd>See
<er>Trillium</er>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Nightshirt</ent>⟦br⟧
